Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
ADDRESS: 1-3 Coondoo Street Corner of Therwine Street, Kuranda, North Queensland 4881

LAND AREA: 2,023m²

FRONTAGE Coondoo Street - 40m, Therwine Street - 50m

RPD There are 24 titles: 
Lots 1-6 on BUP70355
Lots 5-11 on BUP70355
Lots 14-27 on BUP103572

LOCAL AUTHORITY Mareeba Shire Council

ZONE Business

IMPROVEMENTS:
 The site is sloped away from the street front to the lower extremities at the rear of the property. Constructed on-site is a 2-level retail/commercial building fully developed over 100% of the site. The retai larea is at street level with the flats and car park in the lower semi-basement level which is open fully on 2 sides for extensive natural light and ventilation

There are:
- 11 street front shops on the exterior
- 12 internal shops
- 7 market stalls in the central courtyard
- 30 tenancies in total
- 8 x 1-bedroom flats in the semi-basement along with 35
car parks
- Some of the individual 24 titles have more than one tenant
- The total Net Lettable Area is 1,556m²*
*approx

The complex is built as a large square area with a common covered central area for market stalls.

CONSTRUCTION:
-  Re-enforced concrete slabs to all levels
- Concrete masonry block & weatherboard walls to exterior
- Colourbond roof. Most shops have open rake ceilings
- 2 sets of stairs link the retail street area with the lower level
  car park and flats
- Open/roller shutters shop fronts
- 2 sets of tenancy toilets. Public toilets directly across the road
  in the Town Square
- Each shop has separately metered power
- Some air-conditioners supplied
- Wi-Fi/security cameras/ATM on site
- Trading each day between 9am – 4pm
- Council car park at the rear

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: WITHOUT DOUBT THE BEST PERFECTLY POSITIONED PROPERTY IN THE TOURIST "MUST SEE" VILLAGE OF KURANDA

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: One of the main streets in Kuranda

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: An open air cafe and restaurant extending back over the block adjoined by three retail shops all fronting the full 25m frontage of the property. The building is an attractive mix of old and new typifies the classic Kuranda 'look and feel'.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: FULLY LEASED PRIME POSITION KURANDA RETAIL INVESTMENT
